1
00:00:10,300 --> 00:00:11,533
<i> Good morning!</i>

2
00:00:11,667 --> 00:00:12,567
<i> I'm now here, Hazel.</i>

3
00:00:12,700 --> 00:00:13,900
<i> I kept my promise.</i>

4
00:00:14,033 --> 00:00:15,633
<i>When will Timo take back
his statement?</i>

5
00:00:15,767 --> 00:00:17,033
<i> Don't worry.</i>

6
00:00:17,167 --> 00:00:18,733
<i> I won't break our deal.</i>

7
00:00:18,867 --> 00:00:19,967
<i> I'm scared...</i>

8
00:00:20,100 --> 00:00:22,133
<i>Because I already lied,
and now I'll take it back?</i>

9
00:00:22,267 --> 00:00:24,200
<i>If you don't want problems
for your family,</i>

10
00:00:24,333 --> 00:00:25,967
<i> just do what I say.</i>

11
00:00:26,100 --> 00:00:27,533
<i> My god, Hazel.</i>

12
00:00:27,667 --> 00:00:30,033
<i>It's like Jessica's death
means nothing to you.</i>

13
00:00:30,167 --> 00:00:31,900
<i> Everything you're doing</i>

14
00:00:32,033 --> 00:00:34,867
<i>has nothing to do with
the justice you say</i>

15
00:00:35,033 --> 00:00:36,300
<i> you want for Jessica.</i>

16
00:00:36,433 --> 00:00:39,333
<i>It's just all about you
taking Manuel back!</i>

17
00:00:39,467 --> 00:00:41,367
<i>Ma'am Felma hasn't been
leaving her room,</i>

18
00:00:41,500 --> 00:00:44,300
<i> just like Coleen.</i>

19
00:00:44,433 --> 00:00:46,167
<i> It's been days.</i>

20
00:00:46,300 --> 00:00:48,467
<i> So, what's the good news?</i>

21
00:00:48,600 --> 00:00:50,000
<i> She finally came out earlier.</i>

22
00:00:50,133 --> 00:00:52,200
<i>But food wasn't the first thing
she looked for.</i>

23
00:00:52,333 --> 00:00:53,867
<i> Alcohol, Sir Noah.</i>

24
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:56,667
<i> Bro, what happened this time?</i>

25
00:00:56,800 --> 00:00:58,967
<i> Why are you with Hazel again?</i>

26
00:00:59,100 --> 00:01:01,667
<i>Hazel has nothing to do
with my decision.</i>

27
00:01:02,667 --> 00:01:04,533
<i> I went back to her on my own.</i>

28
00:01:04,667 --> 00:01:05,867
<i> I'm just asking one thing.</i>

29
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:07,933
<i> Don't talk to them for now.</i>

30
00:01:08,100 --> 00:01:12,667
<i>If you can't do that, then maybe
you should just go back to them.</i>

31
00:01:12,800 --> 00:01:14,567
<i> Let's just drop our agreement.</i>

32
00:01:43,433 --> 00:01:44,633
Oh.

33
00:02:14,200 --> 00:02:15,400
Felma.

34
00:02:17,700 --> 00:02:19,133
Noah, why are you here?

35
00:02:20,933 --> 00:02:23,900
Didang said
you haven't eaten yet.

36
00:02:24,533 --> 00:02:27,033
Good thing I brought food.

37
00:02:28,400 --> 00:02:30,067
- Come on.
- I don't have the appetite.

38
00:02:31,967 --> 00:02:33,900
You know, you shouldn't
drink alcohol...

39
00:02:34,033 --> 00:02:36,433
- I said I'm not hungry
- on an empty stomach.

40
00:02:36,567 --> 00:02:37,700
Come on, let me.

41
00:02:39,267 --> 00:02:40,367
Here.

42
00:02:41,733 --> 00:02:43,000
Put that aside first.

43
00:02:44,700 --> 00:02:48,067
Let's eat,
then we'll drink after.

44
00:02:55,200 --> 00:02:56,333
Do you remember...

45
00:02:57,667 --> 00:02:59,533
when we first met?

46
00:03:00,467 --> 00:03:02,633
<i> Ah! Get out of there!</i>

47
00:03:02,767 --> 00:03:04,000
<i> Hey! Miss!</i>

48
00:03:04,733 --> 00:03:05,833
<i> What are you doing?</i>

49
00:03:06,667 --> 00:03:07,400
<i> Are you drunk?</i>

50
00:03:07,800 --> 00:03:10,200
<i>Why do you care?
It's none of your business!</i>

51
00:03:10,333 --> 00:03:11,500
I'd had a few drinks.

52
00:03:16,967 --> 00:03:18,367
You were drunk.

53
00:03:18,500 --> 00:03:19,833
Not just tipsy.

54
00:03:19,967 --> 00:03:20,533
- Drunk?
- Yes.

55
00:03:20,700 --> 00:03:21,933
More than just tipsy.

56
00:03:22,067 --> 00:03:24,267
No, I wasn't.

57
00:03:25,600 --> 00:03:26,933
No.

58
00:03:28,167 --> 00:03:29,467
Felma, I remember it.

59
00:03:29,600 --> 00:03:30,567
You were drunk.

60
00:03:32,933 --> 00:03:33,967
Maybe, yes.

61
00:03:34,767 --> 00:03:39,200
Because I was a mess back then.

62
00:03:40,933 --> 00:03:42,367
That was when...

63
00:03:43,967 --> 00:03:46,367
that was when Manuel left me.

64
00:03:48,033 --> 00:03:49,200
<i> You're Hazel?</i>

65
00:03:49,633 --> 00:03:51,733
<i> Hazel Capistrano.</i>

66
00:03:51,867 --> 00:03:54,367
<i> And may I add? Cruz.</i>

67
00:03:54,533 --> 00:03:56,700
<i>Because I'm now
Mrs. Manuel Cruz.</i>

68
00:03:56,833 --> 00:03:58,500
<i> Manuel and I are married.</i>

69
00:04:03,833 --> 00:04:06,600
It's like it's happening all
over again.

70
00:04:06,733 --> 00:04:07,700
It's like it's happening again.

71
00:04:07,833 --> 00:04:11,133
Look, here I am drinking again.

72
00:04:11,267 --> 00:04:13,133
Because I've been left again.

73
00:04:16,433 --> 00:04:17,900
Felma, what happened?

74
00:04:26,367 --> 00:04:29,100
Felma. Felma.

75
00:04:30,367 --> 00:04:33,200
Felma...

76
00:04:34,700 --> 00:04:36,533
Let it out, all the anger...

77
00:04:38,067 --> 00:04:41,033
the pain, the hurt, everything.

78
00:04:41,167 --> 00:04:42,733
Felma, I'm listening.

79
00:04:43,967 --> 00:04:45,933
I'm listening.

80
00:04:46,067 --> 00:04:47,867
Felma, you have me.

81
00:04:48,900 --> 00:04:50,567
I'm here.

82
00:04:52,467 --> 00:04:54,033
I'm listening.

83
00:05:06,367 --> 00:05:08,367
So Manuel only went back
to Hazel...

84
00:05:09,900 --> 00:05:11,500
because of the deal?

85
00:05:11,633 --> 00:05:12,700
Yes.

86
00:05:12,833 --> 00:05:15,133
And you agreed? Why?

87
00:05:15,267 --> 00:05:17,367
Did I even have a choice, Noah?

88
00:05:17,500 --> 00:05:19,033
None, right?

89
00:05:19,167 --> 00:05:20,267
Felma, calm down.

90
00:05:21,633 --> 00:05:26,333
If I had stopped Manuel, Coleen
would've gone to jail.

91
00:05:28,633 --> 00:05:30,000
Felma...

92
00:05:30,133 --> 00:05:32,533
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

93
00:05:34,900 --> 00:05:36,400
My head just hurts so much.

94
00:05:39,333 --> 00:05:42,400
If it were you...
If you were in my situation

95
00:05:43,433 --> 00:05:44,767
who would you choose?

96
00:05:46,033 --> 00:05:47,400
Of course, Coleen.

97
00:05:47,533 --> 00:05:51,133
But Felma,
Hazel is manipulating you.

98
00:05:51,267 --> 00:05:54,167
If she's claiming
she can convince Timo

99
00:05:54,300 --> 00:05:57,000
to take back his statement,
that means...

100
00:05:57,133 --> 00:06:00,500
It means Hazel herself ordered
him to frame Coleen.

101
00:06:02,500 --> 00:06:04,733
We know that,
Manuel and I both do.

102
00:06:06,233 --> 00:06:07,900
But we don't have evidence.

103
00:06:10,667 --> 00:06:14,467
We don't have evidence!
We don't have evidence!

104
00:06:31,967 --> 00:06:33,133
Manuel.

105
00:06:33,267 --> 00:06:35,067
I made chicken pastil.

106
00:06:35,200 --> 00:06:37,000
Jessica's favorite, remember?

107
00:06:37,967 --> 00:06:38,967
Go eat.

108
00:06:40,767 --> 00:06:44,067
<i>Oh my god!
You cooked my favorite!</i>

109
00:06:44,200 --> 00:06:45,033
<i> Well, of course.</i>

110
00:06:45,167 --> 00:06:46,333
<i> So you'll enjoy eating.</i>

111
00:06:46,467 --> 00:06:48,333
<i>And so you can study
well, right?</i>

112
00:06:50,467 --> 00:06:52,367
I'm just not sure
if I got the taste right,

113
00:06:52,500 --> 00:06:55,633
since you used to cook
for Jessica.

114
00:06:55,767 --> 00:06:57,567
Can you stop using Jessica?

115
00:06:58,600 --> 00:07:00,100
I'm already here,
I came back to you.

116
00:07:01,333 --> 00:07:02,633
You even have
my phone now, right?

117
00:07:02,767 --> 00:07:04,800
See? You don't need
to impress me.

118
00:07:06,233 --> 00:07:07,267
You're being mean.

119
00:07:08,900 --> 00:07:10,967
I'm not trying
to impress you, Manuel.

120
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:17,867
I just want you to feel
the love and care.

121
00:07:19,500 --> 00:07:23,233
The things I couldn't
give you before.

122
00:07:23,967 --> 00:07:27,567
If you can't
appreciate my effort...

123
00:07:29,800 --> 00:07:31,700
at least acknowledge it.

124
00:07:32,800 --> 00:07:33,967
Don't reject it.

125
00:07:34,967 --> 00:07:36,100
And I hope...

126
00:07:38,300 --> 00:07:39,833
you talk to me properly.

127
00:07:53,700 --> 00:07:54,833
I hope you like it.

128
00:07:54,967 --> 00:07:56,500
- Here....
- It's okay, I'll do it.

129
00:07:58,233 --> 00:07:59,167
All right.

130
00:08:00,467 --> 00:08:01,600
I'll go back to work.

131
00:08:03,133 --> 00:08:04,267
What work?

132
00:08:04,833 --> 00:08:06,133
Medical transcription.

133
00:08:07,133 --> 00:08:09,100
Miles offered me my old job
back at Southcrest,

134
00:08:09,233 --> 00:08:11,233
but I chose to work from home

135
00:08:12,167 --> 00:08:13,467
so I can focus on you.

136
00:08:14,200 --> 00:08:17,033
And so I can go with you
to your therapy sessions.

137
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:32,300
Dad, please answer.

138
00:08:48,367 --> 00:08:49,400
You brought that?

139
00:08:49,767 --> 00:08:51,167
Andrea won't be here
for another hour.

140
00:08:51,300 --> 00:08:52,800
Let's just chill while we wait.

141
00:08:58,400 --> 00:08:59,433
Why the long face?

142
00:09:00,833 --> 00:09:02,300
Dad's not answering.

143
00:09:02,433 --> 00:09:03,767
I wanted to check on him.

144
00:09:04,133 --> 00:09:06,967
Hazel's probably hovering
over him again.

145
00:09:07,100 --> 00:09:09,600
Or she confiscated his phone

146
00:09:09,733 --> 00:09:12,467
so she can cut Uncle Manuel off
from your lives completely.

147
00:09:12,600 --> 00:09:13,733
I get it.

148
00:09:15,367 --> 00:09:16,367
I expected that already.

149
00:09:16,500 --> 00:09:18,233
That's why I gave Dad
an extra phone.

150
00:09:26,033 --> 00:09:28,433
Manuel! What are you...
Let me do that!

151
00:09:28,600 --> 00:09:30,400
- Let me handle it!
- It's fine, Hazel.

152
00:09:30,533 --> 00:09:32,000
- I got it.
- Hazel, please.

153
00:09:32,133 --> 00:09:33,900
Don't make me feel
like I'm useless.

154
00:09:36,267 --> 00:09:37,233
<i> Come on, come on, please,</i>

155
00:09:37,367 --> 00:09:39,033
<i>- Join me
- No. I said no.</i>

156
00:09:39,167 --> 00:09:40,167
<i>- Here...
- Just eat first.</i>

157
00:09:40,300 --> 00:09:41,200
<i> Wait.</i>

158
00:09:43,800 --> 00:09:46,133
Manuel, please,
don't bring up

159
00:09:46,267 --> 00:09:47,267
what I did back then.

160
00:09:51,100 --> 00:09:52,300
Let me do it.

161
00:11:02,400 --> 00:11:03,967
- Dad, answer...
- No, don't.

162
00:11:04,600 --> 00:11:05,767
- What are you doing?
- Stop, stop, stop!

163
00:11:05,900 --> 00:11:07,200
Don't! What's wrong with you?

164
00:11:07,333 --> 00:11:08,800
Don't call Uncle Manuel.

165
00:11:09,700 --> 00:11:10,967
Hazel might catch him.

166
00:11:12,033 --> 00:11:13,733
It's better if you just wait
for him to call.

167
00:11:14,767 --> 00:11:15,467
Here.

168
00:11:19,333 --> 00:11:20,300
Hazel, what is it?

169
00:11:23,267 --> 00:11:24,900
Oh, nothing.

170
00:11:25,900 --> 00:11:26,833
Are you done eating?

171
00:11:26,967 --> 00:11:28,067
Do you want me to slice
this for you?

172
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:29,767
- No, I'm good.
- Some fruit?

173
00:11:30,267 --> 00:11:31,567
Ah, okay.

174
00:11:37,733 --> 00:11:40,300
You're right, thanks.

175
00:11:42,433 --> 00:11:45,933
Bro, was it really okay
for you and Aunt Felma

176
00:11:46,067 --> 00:11:48,467
to hide the truth
from Andrea and Coleen?

177
00:11:49,700 --> 00:11:51,300
I don't know.

178
00:11:51,433 --> 00:11:54,233
We just had to follow
Dad's request.

179
00:11:54,367 --> 00:11:58,233
I'm just worried because
I can't keep this from Andrea.

180
00:11:58,367 --> 00:11:59,900
Why not?

181
00:12:00,033 --> 00:12:04,767
Because when Andrea
stayed at my condo,

182
00:12:04,900 --> 00:12:06,000
I saw how much she suffered.

183
00:12:06,133 --> 00:12:07,333
How angry she was
at Uncle Manuel.

184
00:12:07,467 --> 00:12:09,633
And I don't want to see her
like that again.

185
00:12:11,667 --> 00:12:12,867
I get you.

186
00:12:13,667 --> 00:12:14,833
I see it, too.

187
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:17,867
But we really need
to follow Dad.

188
00:12:18,700 --> 00:12:21,633
If my sisters find out
about this deal...

189
00:12:22,800 --> 00:12:24,233
things could get messy, Joel.

190
00:12:25,833 --> 00:12:27,033
Especially since nothing's
happening yet

191
00:12:27,167 --> 00:12:28,200
with Coleen's case.

192
00:12:29,567 --> 00:12:31,933
Timo hasn't even taken back
his statement.

193
00:12:40,567 --> 00:12:41,867
Oh! Dear lord!

194
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:43,367
I thought you were
an apparition!

195
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:45,033
Ah...

196
00:12:48,300 --> 00:12:52,567
Good thing you finally came out
of your room.

197
00:12:52,700 --> 00:12:55,333
I know this is hard for you,

198
00:12:55,467 --> 00:12:59,033
but I just want you
to know I'm here.

199
00:12:59,167 --> 00:13:02,033
You can talk to me anytime.

200
00:13:02,167 --> 00:13:06,700
How about now? Since I'm also
dealing with stuff myself.

201
00:13:08,400 --> 00:13:11,400
We can share
our problems, right?

202
00:13:11,533 --> 00:13:12,700
I'll go first.

203
00:13:23,033 --> 00:13:24,933
Coleen, remember JB?

204
00:13:26,567 --> 00:13:29,100
The one from the resort?

205
00:13:29,233 --> 00:13:31,467
Well, I just found out
on FriendsBook

206
00:13:32,333 --> 00:13:34,200
just noow...

207
00:13:35,600 --> 00:13:39,667
that he's taken!

208
00:13:41,433 --> 00:13:42,933
He already...

209
00:13:43,067 --> 00:13:45,700
he already has a boyfriend!

210
00:13:47,100 --> 00:13:50,533
From the same resort!

211
00:13:57,000 --> 00:13:58,133
That's it.

212
00:13:58,267 --> 00:14:00,033
I shared mine,
Your turn.

213
00:14:01,033 --> 00:14:02,867
I'm okay, Didang.

214
00:14:05,300 --> 00:14:07,233
I'm just worried about Mom.

215
00:14:08,667 --> 00:14:10,667
I hope she's all right.

216
00:14:10,967 --> 00:14:12,200
You know what, yes.

217
00:14:12,333 --> 00:14:15,533
I'm worried about
Ma'am Felma, too.

218
00:14:15,667 --> 00:14:19,067
How long will
she stay like this?

219
00:14:19,200 --> 00:14:21,000
And then... Oh.

220
00:14:21,667 --> 00:14:22,833
- Sweetheart.
- Ma'am.

221
00:14:22,967 --> 00:14:24,133
Have you eaten?

222
00:14:24,967 --> 00:14:26,700
How about your sister
and brother?

223
00:14:26,833 --> 00:14:28,100
Aren't they home yet?

224
00:14:28,267 --> 00:14:30,667
I already called Andrea, Ma'am.

225
00:14:30,800 --> 00:14:32,533
She said she's working overtime.

226
00:14:32,667 --> 00:14:34,333
And Jeffrey said

227
00:14:34,467 --> 00:14:37,567
he'll wait for Andrea,
so they'll go home together.

228
00:14:37,700 --> 00:14:40,533
So it's just us for dinner?

229
00:14:41,633 --> 00:14:43,033
Ah...

230
00:14:43,533 --> 00:14:46,000
Noah, why don't you have
dinner here, too?

231
00:14:46,133 --> 00:14:49,133
Sure, sure.

232
00:14:49,267 --> 00:14:50,400
Ah, all right, wait.

233
00:14:50,533 --> 00:14:52,467
I'll just get
my headache medicine.

234
00:14:52,600 --> 00:14:53,700
Oh, Didang.

235
00:14:53,833 --> 00:14:54,500
- Yes, Ma'am?
- Set the table

236
00:14:54,633 --> 00:14:55,733
for the four of us.

237
00:14:55,867 --> 00:14:57,033
Yes, Ma'am.

238
00:14:57,167 --> 00:14:58,133
Okay.

239
00:15:00,233 --> 00:15:01,333
Oh?

240
00:15:02,367 --> 00:15:03,467
Wow...

241
00:15:03,600 --> 00:15:05,533
what kind of magic did you use
on Ma'am Felma, Sir Noah?

242
00:15:05,667 --> 00:15:06,933
Why does she look okay now?

243
00:15:08,600 --> 00:15:10,367
Come on,
I just talked to her.

244
00:15:14,867 --> 00:15:16,300
Coleen, sweetheart,
how about you?

245
00:15:16,433 --> 00:15:17,800
How are you feeling?

246
00:15:47,567 --> 00:15:51,200
<i>Dad, you'll never be
a burden to me.</i>

247
00:15:51,333 --> 00:15:53,467
<i>And I don't mind taking care
of you, Dad.</i>

248
00:15:53,600 --> 00:15:55,667
<i>Remember, ever since
I was a baby,</i>

249
00:15:55,800 --> 00:15:57,533
<i> you took good care of me.</i>

250
00:15:57,667 --> 00:15:59,100
<i>Then I'll just stay
in a nursing home for now.</i>

251
00:15:59,233 --> 00:16:02,133
<i> Dad, no.</i>

252
00:16:02,267 --> 00:16:05,133
<i>I don't want that, Dad,
I won't allow it.</i>

253
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:08,967
<i>I'll do everything to bring you
home to the Philippines.</i>

254
00:16:09,500 --> 00:16:10,967
<i> Love you, Dad.</i>

255
00:16:30,900 --> 00:16:32,467
I miss her every day.

256
00:16:36,533 --> 00:16:38,367
And every day, I feel guilty.

257
00:16:41,300 --> 00:16:43,267
Because you kept
hurting her, Hazel!

258
00:16:44,967 --> 00:16:46,033
Yes.

259
00:16:46,900 --> 00:16:48,100
I know.

260
00:16:48,733 --> 00:16:50,467
I wasn't a good mother.

261
00:16:52,500 --> 00:16:53,733
And what hurts the most is...

262
00:16:56,900 --> 00:16:58,900
I'll never have the chance
to make it up to her.

263
00:17:00,867 --> 00:17:02,067
Ever again.

264
00:17:06,967 --> 00:17:09,367
Not once did I make her
feel my love.

265
00:17:11,167 --> 00:17:13,600
Unlike you...

266
00:17:13,733 --> 00:17:17,300
You showed our daughter
every single day

267
00:17:17,467 --> 00:17:18,700
how much you loved her.

268
00:17:20,433 --> 00:17:21,733
Thank you, Manuel.

269
00:17:23,133 --> 00:17:24,833
You loved her so deeply.

270
00:17:27,233 --> 00:17:28,367
Even though...

271
00:17:31,200 --> 00:17:32,400
Even though what, Hazel?

272
00:17:34,733 --> 00:17:36,467
<i>You're so lucky
to have Charles, you know?</i>

273
00:17:36,600 --> 00:17:37,900
<i> He loves you.</i>

274
00:17:38,033 --> 00:17:39,467
<i> Don't worry.</i>

275
00:17:39,600 --> 00:17:41,233
<i>You'll find someone
like him, too.</i>

276
00:17:42,233 --> 00:17:45,867
<i>I think I already have someone
who can help me raise my baby.</i>

277
00:17:46,300 --> 00:17:50,333
<i>You think he'll still
fight for you</i>

278
00:17:50,500 --> 00:17:52,600
<i>once he finds out you're not
his real daughter?</i>

279
00:17:54,800 --> 00:17:55,933
Even though...

280
00:17:58,633 --> 00:18:00,133
you already had kids before.

281
00:18:03,167 --> 00:18:04,933
You treated her like a princess.

282
00:18:07,667 --> 00:18:12,567
You made her feel like she was
the only one in your life.

283
00:18:15,167 --> 00:18:20,667
You gave her more
than enough love.

284
00:18:25,133 --> 00:18:26,367
Manuel...

285
00:18:34,167 --> 00:18:37,700
Manuel, I'll be grateful to you
for the rest of my life.

286
00:18:39,567 --> 00:18:41,433
Because you loved our daughter.

287
00:18:43,000 --> 00:18:45,067
Even for the short time
she was here...

288
00:18:47,400 --> 00:18:48,700
you made her happy.

289
00:18:49,567 --> 00:18:51,500
You made her whole...

290
00:18:52,633 --> 00:18:53,967
thank you so much.

291
00:18:56,833 --> 00:18:58,767
Go back to your work.

292
00:19:31,067 --> 00:19:34,733
Wow! So good!

293
00:19:34,867 --> 00:19:36,567
The purple yam is so good!

294
00:19:37,600 --> 00:19:39,167
Order more, Didang, okay?

295
00:19:39,300 --> 00:19:40,933
Really, Ma'am?
You like it that much?

296
00:19:41,067 --> 00:19:42,667
But didn't you say
you hate that stuff?

297
00:19:42,800 --> 00:19:45,933
You even said it's so sweet
it'll give you diabetes.

298
00:19:46,500 --> 00:19:47,667
Did I say that?

299
00:19:47,933 --> 00:19:49,000
No!

300
00:19:49,133 --> 00:19:50,400
It's delicious!

301
00:19:50,633 --> 00:19:51,933
The sweetness is just right.

302
00:19:52,400 --> 00:19:54,333
Wow, she's making me
look like a liar.

303
00:19:56,100 --> 00:19:57,167
Come on, Didang!

304
00:19:59,667 --> 00:20:03,167
How about the dish I asked you
to cook for Jeff?

305
00:20:03,800 --> 00:20:05,333
It's done.

306
00:20:09,033 --> 00:20:10,133
Delicious.

307
00:20:10,600 --> 00:20:11,500
Mom.

308
00:20:11,633 --> 00:20:12,533
- Oh.
- Hi.

309
00:20:12,667 --> 00:20:13,900
Oh, sweetheart.

310
00:20:15,167 --> 00:20:17,033
I shouldn't have
worked overtime,

311
00:20:17,167 --> 00:20:19,433
so we could've eaten together.

312
00:20:19,567 --> 00:20:21,800
Oh no, that's fine, sweetheart.

313
00:20:22,967 --> 00:20:25,067
I actually thought
you two would be home later.

314
00:20:25,200 --> 00:20:26,600
We ended up finishing the food.

315
00:20:26,733 --> 00:20:30,967
Good thing Didang already cooked
the rest of the dishes.

316
00:20:31,100 --> 00:20:32,500
Go on, sit.

317
00:20:33,667 --> 00:20:34,533
I'll handle it.

318
00:20:34,700 --> 00:20:36,367
- Good evening po.
- Oh.

319
00:20:36,500 --> 00:20:37,900
Hi, Joel.

320
00:20:38,033 --> 00:20:40,233
Didang, serve the dishes, okay?

321
00:20:40,367 --> 00:20:41,333
Ah, okay, Ma'am.

322
00:20:42,667 --> 00:20:44,300
It's so fun.

323
00:20:44,433 --> 00:20:46,733
There are many of us.

324
00:20:46,867 --> 00:20:50,967
We should've invited Paz
and Abel, too.

325
00:20:53,200 --> 00:20:54,500
Mom, what did you eat?

326
00:20:54,633 --> 00:20:57,000
You're like... super hyper?

327
00:20:58,733 --> 00:21:00,667
You know what, son,
it must be the yam.

328
00:21:00,800 --> 00:21:01,967
She ate a lot of it.

329
00:21:02,600 --> 00:21:04,000
And she said it
wasn't even sweet.

330
00:21:04,633 --> 00:21:08,233
Mom, didn't you hate
that purple yam?

331
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:12,567
You said it's just sugar
with a little yam.

332
00:21:12,700 --> 00:21:14,133
And a one-way ticket to
diabetes.

333
00:21:14,267 --> 00:21:16,533
Exactly, Andrea.

334
00:21:16,667 --> 00:21:20,567
It's like Ma'am Felma forgot
how overly sweet

335
00:21:20,700 --> 00:21:22,867
that yam I bought is.

336
00:21:27,567 --> 00:21:28,633
Didang!

337
00:21:28,767 --> 00:21:29,767
What's that?

338
00:21:30,800 --> 00:21:33,333
Pork adobo? Why?

339
00:21:33,467 --> 00:21:35,500
Ma'am, that's what
you asked me to cook.

340
00:21:35,633 --> 00:21:37,933
No! Chicken!

341
00:21:38,067 --> 00:21:40,100
I told you
to make chicken adobo!

342
00:21:41,200 --> 00:21:44,433
Ma'am, you're too young...

343
00:21:45,633 --> 00:21:47,000
to be forgetting things,
aren't you?

344
00:21:47,133 --> 00:21:49,500
But you really told me
to cook pork adobo.

345
00:21:49,633 --> 00:21:51,600
I even asked you, Ma'am.
I said.

346
00:21:51,733 --> 00:21:53,500
"Should I mix chicken
and pork together?"

347
00:21:53,633 --> 00:21:55,233
You told me, pork only.

348
00:21:55,367 --> 00:21:56,700
What are you trying to imply?

349
00:21:58,100 --> 00:21:59,533
That I'm lying?

350
00:22:08,300 --> 00:22:11,400
I hope you can attend
Coleen's hearing.

351
00:22:11,533 --> 00:22:12,433
Of course.

352
00:22:12,567 --> 00:22:14,000
I already moved my schedules.

353
00:22:14,833 --> 00:22:15,833
Thank you.

354
00:22:16,000 --> 00:22:17,733
Your support means a lot.

355
00:22:17,867 --> 00:22:20,500
Especially now that Manuel
isn't with us.

356
00:22:20,633 --> 00:22:22,633
It's like I have to report every
single thing to you.

357
00:22:22,767 --> 00:22:24,967
Why don't you just tell me
if you want to put me in chains?

358
00:22:25,100 --> 00:22:27,867
I was just thinking
you might need my help.

359
00:22:28,000 --> 00:22:29,867
No, not if it's coming from you.

360
00:22:31,467 --> 00:22:32,467
Mom...

361
00:22:33,667 --> 00:22:35,167
My head just hurts.

362
00:22:35,300 --> 00:22:36,633
Maybe you need to rest.

363
00:22:37,200 --> 00:22:38,633
Jessica's gone, Dad.

364
00:22:38,767 --> 00:22:41,000
But Jeff, Coleen,
and I are still here.

365
00:22:41,133 --> 00:22:42,100
Why, Andrea?

366
00:22:42,233 --> 00:22:43,667
What did your mother tell you?

367
00:22:43,800 --> 00:22:44,700
You two aren't talking?

368
00:22:44,833 --> 00:22:46,133
What exactly are we supposed
to talk about?

369
00:22:46,267 --> 00:22:47,967
That you were hurting yourself,

370
00:22:48,100 --> 00:22:50,000
so he had to come back here
for you?

371
00:22:50,167 --> 00:22:51,933
Is that what they told you?
